<HEADLINE>
FT  24 DEC 94 / Weekend Money: CGT indexation allowances - November
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The table shows capital gains tax indexation allowances for assets sold in
November. Multiply the original cost of the asset by the figure for the
month in which you bought it. Subtract the result from the proceeds of your
sale: the balance will be your taxable gain or loss. Suppose you bought
shares for Pounds 6,000 in November 1985 and sold them in November 1994 for
Pounds 13,000. Multiplying the original cost by the November 1985 figure of
1.519 gives a total of Pounds 9,090. Subtracting that from Pounds 13,000
gives a capital gain of Pounds 3,910 which is within the CGT allowance of
Pounds 5,800. If selling shares bought before April 6 1982, you should use
the March 1982 figure. The RPI in November 1994 was 145.3.
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
        1982     1983     1984     1985     1986     1987     1988
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Jan        -    1.759    1.673    1.593    1.510    1.453    1.407
Feb        -    1.751    1.666    1.580    1.504    1.447    1.401
