<HEADLINE>
FT  24 DEC 94 / Weekend Money (Companies): New issues
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A quiet week in the new issues market was enlivened by the news that BAS
International Holdings, a supplier of low-cost soft toys, stationery and
giftware, intends to float in the new year.
BAS, which is based in Manchester, is hoping for a market capitalisation of
between Pounds 20m and Pounds 30m after its debut. It plans to raise about
Pounds 12m through the float.
The company said that the money raised will be used to fund organic growth
in the distribution business, and help finance a new regional distribution
centre in north-west England.
BAS is owned by Martin Abramson, chairman and founder, who has a 70 per cent
stake, and Tyrone Farber and Richard Rosenburg, both managing directors, who
hold 15 per cent each.
The company, which operates through four subsidiaries, had total annual
sales of around Pounds 22m and pre-tax profits for 1994 are forecast at
Pounds 2m, against Pounds 992,000.
