   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Patrick Mayhew, the Northern Ireland secretary, has hinted that the
Royal Ulster Constabulary may eventually be cut to little more than a
quarter of its present strength, David Owen writes.
