trafficking meant the province needed at least 7,500 police officers. He
said he doubted if a reduction to even this level would be achieved in the
next five years.
The Rev William McCrea of the hardline Democratic Unionist party said Sir
Patrick was talking about a 'hypothetical situation'. He added: 'There is
not a genuine peace.'
