   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mercury Communications, the UK's second biggest public telecommunications
operator, yesterday made substantial cuts in international call prices for
its largest users in reaction to intensifying competition, Alan Cane writes.
It said daytime telephone calls to north America would come down 55 per
cent, to 20p a minute from 44p, for customers spending Pounds 35,000 or more
